1. *Platili* smo račun u restoranu pre nego što smo otišli. (We *paid* the bill at the restaurant before we left.)
2. Oni su *platili* previše novca za taj automobil. (They *paid* too much money for that car.)
3. Ja ne bih *platio* toliko za tu haljinu. (I wouldn't *pay* that much for that dress.)
4. Moji roditelji su mi *platili* letovanje. (My parents *paid* for my vacation.)
5. *Plaćeni* radnik ima više prava od neplaćenog volontera. (A *paid* worker has more rights than an unpaid volunteer.)
6. Kupili smo novi televizor i sada ga moramo *platiti* na rate. (We bought a new TV and now we have to *pay* for it in installments.)
7. Čim sam *platio* račun, otišao sam kući. (As soon as I *paid* the bill, I went home.)
8. Oni su *platili* kaznu zbog prekoračenja brzine. (They *paid* a fine for speeding.)
9. Da biste pristupili ovom sadržaju, morate *platiti* pretplatu. (To access this content, you need to *pay* a subscription.)
10. Ukoliko ne *platite* račun na vreme, biće vam uvedene kamate. (If you don't *pay* the bill on time, you will be charged interest.)